By no later than December 31 of each year, in an advertisement at least one-fourth (1/4) of a page in size, the Kentucky Lottery Corporation shall publish the following information in every general-circulation daily newspaper published in Kentucky:
The statements of revenue, expenses, and changes in retained earnings as shown in the most recent annual audit report. It shall be explained that the transfer of dividends is the amount of lottery earnings transferred to the general fund;
A statement identifying the auditing firm;
A telephone number which citizens may call to obtain a complete copy of the annual audit report; and
The name of the president/chief executive officer of the Kentucky Lottery Corporation and a complete list of board members. The Kentucky Lottery Corporation shall pay for the cost of the advertisement.
